import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Opening Prices')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='open', data=data, label='Opening Price')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, label='Closing Price')
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Price')
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='signal', y='ret', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between signal and returns?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['ret'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['ret'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
